# Plan: Add `mistral-instruct-v3` Specialized Chat Template Handler

## Context

llama.cpp supports specialized chat template handlers that bypass the generic Jinja autoparser for models with well-known, fixed prompt formats. This plan adds a handler for **Mistral Instruct v0.3**, used by models like Mistral-7B-Instruct-v0.3. The v0.3 format uses `[INST]`/`[/INST]` delimiters and prepends the system prompt to the first user turn. A specialized handler avoids Jinja overhead and produces exact output.

---

## Critical Files

- **`common/chat.cpp`** — all handler implementations and detection logic (only file to modify)
- **`common/chat.h`** — `common_chat_format` enum (`COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_CONTENT_ONLY` already exists, no changes needed)

---

## Implementation Steps

### Step 1 — Add the handler function in `common/chat.cpp`

**Insert location:** After the `common_chat_params_init_gigachat_v3` function ends at **line 1517** (before `namespace workaround` at line 1519).

**Code to insert:**

```cpp
static common_chat_params common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(
        const common_chat_template & /* tmpl */,
        const autoparser::generation_params & inputs) {

    common_chat_params data;

    std::string system_prompt;
    bool first_user = true;

    for (const auto & msg : inputs.messages) {
        const auto role    = msg.value("role", "");
        const auto content = msg.value("content", "");

        if (role == "system") {
            system_prompt = content;
        } else if (role == "user") {
            if (first_user) {
                data.prompt += "<s>";
                first_user = false;
            }
            std::string inst_content = content;
            if (!system_prompt.empty()) {
                inst_content = system_prompt + "\n" + content;
                system_prompt.clear();
            }
            data.prompt += "[INST] " + inst_content + " [/INST]";
        } else if (role == "assistant") {
            data.prompt += " " + content + "</s>";
        }
    }

    data.format = COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_CONTENT_ONLY;

    return data;
}
```

**Key details:**
- `/* tmpl */` — template parameter unused since prompt is built manually; unnamed to suppress compiler warnings.
- `using json = nlohmann::ordered_json` alias already exists at line 31; `msg.value(...)` works on `json` objects in the `inputs.messages` array.
- `system_prompt` accumulates any system message, then is prepended to the *first* user turn only (cleared after use).
- `first_user` flag gates the single `<s>` BOS insertion at the very start.
- Multi-turn format produced:
  - With system: `<s>[INST] {system}\n{user1} [/INST] {assistant1}</s>[INST] {user2} [/INST]`
  - Without system: `<s>[INST] {user1} [/INST] {assistant1}</s>[INST] {user2} [/INST]`
- `data.format = COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_CONTENT_ONLY` — no PEG parser, no grammar, no tool-call handling needed.

---

### Step 2 — Register detection in `common_chat_try_specialized_template()`

**Insert location:** Inside `common_chat_try_specialized_template()` (starts at **line 1634**), after the GigaChatV3 block ending at **line 1688**, and before `return std::nullopt;` at **line 1690**.

**Code to insert:**

```cpp
    // Mistral Instruct v3 - uses [INST]/[/INST] markers without [SYSTEM_PROMPT]
    // Distinguishes from Ministral 3 which uses [SYSTEM_PROMPT] instead
    if (src.find("[INST]") != std::string::npos &&
        src.find("[/INST]") != std::string::npos &&
        src.find("[SYSTEM_PROMPT]") == std::string::npos) {
        LOG_DBG("Using specialized template: Mistral Instruct v3\n");
        return common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(tmpl, params);
    }
```

**Key details:**
- Must check for absence of `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` — the existing Ministral 3 handler (detected first, lines 1640–1644) uses `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` + `[TOOL_CALLS]` + `[ARGS]`. However, since Ministral 3 is checked first and returns early, the `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` exclusion here is a belt-and-suspenders guard for safety and clarity.
- This block goes last (before `std::nullopt`), so it doesn't interfere with any existing handler detections.

---

## Reused Patterns

| Pattern | Source | Usage |
|---|---|---|
| `msg.value("role", "")` | all handlers | field access on `json` message objects |
| `msg.value("content", "")` | all handlers | field access on `json` message objects |
| `data.format = COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_CONTENT_ONLY` | default in `common_chat_params` | simplest format; no PEG/grammar needed |
| `LOG_DBG("Using specialized template: ...\n")` | every detection block | consistent debug logging |
| `src.find(...) != std::string::npos` | every detection | template source string marker checks |

---

